# Professional Homepage Redesign — Techglaz Labs

Redesign the homepage to match a premium EdTech look inspired by the reference screenshot (Learnify-style dark navy hero with yellow accents, split-layout hero with imagery, image-rich course cards). **All existing content stays the same — only the visual design changes.** The company's actual logo images ([logo.png](file:///d:/techglaz_main/public/logo.png), [logo_name.png](file:///d:/techglaz_main/public/logo_name.png)) from `/public` will replace the current text-only logo.

---

## Reference Design Analysis (Screenshot)

The reference shows a **Learnify** EdTech site with these design patterns:

| Section | Design Pattern |
|---------|---------------|
| **Navbar** | Logo + nav links (Home, Courses, Features, Pricing, About) + Login / Sign Up buttons |
| **Hero** | Dark navy background, split layout — left: headline + description + CTA buttons + student avatars row; right: hero illustration/image + floating "Your Progress 78%" card + "Current Lesson" card |
| **Features Row** | Icon bar with 4 items: Expert Instructors, Learn at Your Pace, Certification, Community Support |
| **Course Cards** | Image-topped cards with badges (Bestseller/Hot/New), course title, description, instructor avatar + name, rating stars, lesson count, price |
| **CTA Banner** | Bottom banner "Start Your Learning Journey Today" with Get Started button |

---

## Color Theme — Adapted for Techglaz Labs

Keeping the existing brand palette (**navy #1a3c6e / steel blue #2e75b6 / amber #f59e0b**) but enhancing it to match the reference's premium dark-navy + golden-yellow vibe:

| Role | Current | New | Rationale |
|------|---------|-----|-----------|
| Hero BG | `#090d14` (near-black) | `#0c1524` (rich dark navy) | Matches reference deep navy hero |
| Accent | `#f59e0b` (amber) | `#f59e0b` → keep, plus add `#fbbf24` glow variant | Yellow/gold CTA like reference |
| Feature Bar BG | none | `#132035` (dark blue-gray) | Distinct bar below hero |
| Card Overlay | white/glass | Keep white, add subtle brand-blue top-border accent | Adds premium feel |

> [!NOTE]
> The overall brand palette stays intact — we're enhancing the tone and adding depth, not changing the brand identity.

